I like Adam Sandler movies. Forget the critics, his movies are fun times!!! And this set has four of them!

1) "Click" makes me feel sad after watching it, but that's okay. The sadness is integral to the story like Beverly D'Angelos boobs in "National Lampoon's Vacation."
2) "50 First Dates" gets a little repetitive, but I like Sean Astin so I can deal with that!
3) "Mr. Deeds" has Winona Ryder AND John Turtorro so it's an arthouse flick (Street cred for me for watching it!).
4) "Big Daddy" stars Jon Stewart and features Hooters restaurant so friends on both sides of the political spectrum can appreciate that. It's a win-win.

This is the perfect addition to any film buff looking to diversify his/her DVD library.
